  "important_notes": [
    "BinlogConnector, BinlogConnectorConfig, BinlogConnectorConnection are all abstract — MySQL and MariaDB provide concrete subclasses",
    "BinlogConnector validates connections by running 'SELECT version()' with a timeout via Threads.runWithTimeout()",
    "BinlogOffsetContext tracks both GTID-based and file/position-based offsets; restartXxx fields hold recovery position",
    "BinlogConnectorConnection.validateLogPosition() integrates with OffsetContext to check GTID or binlog file availability",
    "BinlogPartition equality is solely based on serverName (ignores databaseName from AbstractPartition for equals/hashCode)",
    "BinlogConnectorConfig has ignoreGtidOnRecovery flag that causes validateLogPosition to skip GTID check"
  ],

